JOHANNESBURG - National Treasury will hold an independent commission of inquiry into governance issues at the Public Investment Corporation (PIC). Finance Minister Nhlanhla Nene has instructed the board to begin a forensic investigation into allegations against PIC executives. The corporation handles investments on behalf of the Government Employees Pension Fund. READ: The question of the PIC is not just noise: DA It is facing criticism of its governance and investment processes. One of these includes its investments in VBS Mutual Bank, which was placed under curatorship in March. Earlier this week the minister said public trust back in the institution must be restored. The announcement has not mentioned CEO Dan Matjila’s fate. eNCA